  "text": "The Braille document can be printed either single sided or double sided. So dots of a Braille cells on the paper should be on the intersections of an orthogonal grid. In double sided printed document, the dots formed are called Recto dot and Verso dot. As verso dots are slightly shifted, so the grid of verso dots falls between the grid of recto dots [CITATION_1] .",
